{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01WGoX76RHMXqPzyeoVvVMTd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VB23Z9twMy3HhtVdRTKo74","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# spark-pi Namespace — Migration & Upgrade Change Plan\n\nStatus: DRAFT FOR REVIEW — no changes have been applied. Live configuration is\nunchanged. Execution is deferred to an approved change window.\n\nDate: 2026-06-18  |  Scope: namespace `spark-pi`  |  Author: ops migration prep\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (as inspected, baseline)\n\nWorkloads (all on image `apache/spark:3.5.3`, SA `spark-pi`):\n\n| Object | Kind | Key config |\n|---|---|---|\n| spark-master | Deployment | replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi; ports 7077,8080 |\n| spark-worker | Deployment | replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi; env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1 |\n| spark-pi | Job | spark-submit `--master local[2] --driver-memory 512m`, SparkPi partitions=1000, backoffLimit=0 (Completed) |\n\nRBAC: Role `spark-pi-role` (live verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch\non services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, **pods**), RoleBinding\n`spark-pi-role-binding` -> SA `spark-pi`. SA `default` exists but unused.\n\nConfigMaps: `kube-root-ca.crt` (system), `config-audit` (prior read-only audit).\nNetworkPolicies: none. securityContext: `{}` (empty) on all workloads.\n\nKnown findings carried from `config-audit`: F1 securityContext hardening missing\n(HIGH), F2 RBAC over-permission + drift on `pods` (MEDIUM), F3 no NetworkPolicy\n(MEDIUM), F4 mutable image tag / no digest pin (LOW).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Planned Changes (what to change)\n\nC1 [Upgrade] Bump Spark image `apache/spark:3.5.3` -> next approved patch\n   (e.g. 3.5.x latest) pinned by digest `@sha256:...` (addresses F4). Apply\n   uniformly to master, worker, and the Job template.\n\nC2 [Security/F1] Add restricted securityContext to all three workloads:\n   `runAsNonRoot: true`, `runAsUser: <non-zero>`, `allowPrivilegeEscalation:\n   false`, `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` (with emptyDir for /tmp & spark work\n   dirs), `capabilities.drop: [ALL]`, `seccompProfile.type: RuntimeDefault`.\n\nC3 [RBAC/F2] Reconcile Role to declared manifest: remove out-of-band `pods` and\n   trim write verbs (delete/update/patch) not required by the SparkPi batch job.\n   Re-apply from version control to stop drift.\n\nC4 [Network/F3] Add a default-deny NetworkPolicy plus explicit allows for\n   worker->master 7077 and operator access to 8080/8081.\n\nC5 [Hygiene] Remove/retain decision on unused `default` SA automounting; set\n   `automountServiceAccountToken: false` where token not needed.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Order of Execution (lowest-risk first)\n\n1. C4 NetworkPolicy (additive, default-deny last) — validate connectivity first.\n2. C3 RBAC reconcile — confirm Spark job still runs under reduced perms.\n3. C2 securityContext hardening — rolling restart of master/worker.\n4. C1 image upgrade — rolling update master/worker, then re-run Job.\n5. C5 SA token hygiene — final tightening.\n\nRationale: apply isolation and least-privilege before the version bump so the\nupgrade is validated against the hardened baseline; keep the destructive/version\nchange last and easiest to roll back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Verification Per Step\n\n- C4: `kubectl get netpol -n spark-pi`; worker logs show registration to\n  `spark://spark-master:7077`; master 8080 UI reachable from allowed source only.\n- C3: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi <verb>\n  <res> -n spark-pi` matches intended matrix; re-run Job -> Completed.\n- C2: `kubectl get pod -o jsonpath` shows runAsNonRoot/dropped caps; pods reach\n  Running 1/1; no CrashLoop.\n- C1: `kubectl get deploy -o jsonpath='{..image}'` shows new digest; rollout\n  `kubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi`;\n  re-run spark-pi Job, expect log \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" and exit 0.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback\n\nEach change is applied from version-controlled manifests; rollback =\n`kubectl rollout undo` (deployments) or re-apply previous manifest (Role,\nNetworkPolicy, Job). Take `kubectl get all,role,rolebinding,netpol -o yaml`\nsnapshot before the window. backoffLimit=0 on the Job means a failed verification\nrun must be deleted and re-created, not auto-retried.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Approval\n\nThis plan must be reviewed and signed off before any `kubectl apply` is executed.\nNo item above has been applied; the live `spark-pi` namespace remains exactly as\ninspected on 2026-06-18.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1806,"cache_read_input_tokens":34308,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1806},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d47fc9f-97df-4e30-9a3f-a3c5be912fab","uuid":"6beb0dfb-ef73-4df4-871a-e8f537c568f2","request_id":"req_011CcAWwfE2NZCzRPsdHM6Qz"}
